The paper discusses the Majority is Stablest Theorem, which has applications in hardness of approximation and social choice theory, indicating that it could belong to categories such as cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.GT (computational game theory). The use of the Sum of Squares hierarchy suggests a possible connection to cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.IT (information theory).
